        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 25 at 3:15PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles northeast of La Verkin to near Apple
Valley. Movement was northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Zion National Park, Virgin, Springdale, and Rockville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
